[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing javac compile issues**\n\nI’m running into issues with javac compilation failing, possibly due to missing dependencies like maven-artifact. I should check artifact dependencies for optional or provided ones, noting that the POM only provides maven-artifact, which normal consumers get from the Maven site plugin. It looks like the lack of its resolution blocks access to public APIs like createContextForSkin and copyResources. To solve this, I’m thinking I should recommend adding maven-artifact version 3.6.3 along with others like doxia-module-apt and doxia-module-xdoc or fml. I wonder if it's necessary to add multiple dependencies without overcomplicating things!\n\n**Clarifying setup requirements**\n\nOkay, the setup should extend beyond the usual generated test scaffold if I want meaningful coverage. It’s not just optional! If there are no module dependencies, I’m thinking about integrating the xhtml5 module with direct mergeDocument to achieve better results. This approach could make coverage possible, but I want to ensure it aligns with what’s needed for proper functionality. It feels a bit complex, but I'm focused on getting this right!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cb9d6a9bdc34e6b016a3f577accac8190b26627f6ba28f9d4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP1eHnz62dHH94a_He16XJ5o-APYBYtPdXDt4ed7CxRBikOPkHGr5oMKVCodML5C5jN1-eDOku_s4rEtPVBh29vYVdO4g8WZ0Lgl64JK29_dota7eAxkoh7Fh9aibUOOvL7GJOVkDuzUtT6WuDEGUpYEhDCQlSaUWvsmxnEHTgDBqmepLLZmXdV7H8Ln3P1Snmudj9rvJkik8mhDvFH58Q-_wK8mDy-uLQAj-3cVt7jna0h0r3_WSsZtpKdiASbHpj-KADQEhg8hgME7qsvygEK_Hu0ynWb9CRJzSVXuw3kyphyrsyoL6BiVFuPArioflUkVtVCGxBikPM1_gZuRY_c5H6lgCBSD5rPWR5snhCIh_txcZIuNHBlG7Wig85va9wGd2YPdla27wnUwaKSuay7zRMLM04o75PFMnxTStC5DR4th0Yw0fFA-wrFPZHd5_Rg7eXCoS9cxV9G9QFEKLls65TrFJhJuyTWnG2MzAUq513T0h1-7K6M0BXZxat7qhFDYi5-DfsHYXdvrJaPNp4X1juCLWXSV_vEB8B5ELw7OqSoAz